<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> URGENT: Pakistan to Confiscate British-Awarded Land </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, June 11 (Xinhua) -- Pakistani Prime Minister Nawaz
Sharif announced Thursday that his government will confiscate all
the land given to those feudal landlords by the British before the
partition.
</P>
<P>
Unveiling his national agenda in a televised speech Thursday
evening, the prime minister said all the 1.2 million acres (about
486,000 hectares) of land to be confiscated will be re-distributed
among landless poor farmers.
</P>
<P>
It is the first time in Pakistan that the government has
decided to confiscate land from landlords. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
