<DOCNO> XIE19980612.0003 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Clinton's Visit to China is Right For U.S. </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, June 11 (Xinhua) -- U.S. President Bill Clinton
said here Thursday that his visit to China is the right thing to
do since China is making substantial progress in many different
fields and is fulfilling an important role in world and regional
peace.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the National Geographic Society, Clinton said that
over the past 25 years, China has entered a period of profound
change, "Emerging from isolation, turning a closed economy into an
engine for growth, increasing cooperation with the rest of the
world, and raising the standard of living for hundreds of millions
of its citizens."
</P>
<P>
He said China also has played a major role in safeguarding
peace in the Korean peninsula, throughout Asia and the rest of the
world as well.
</P>
<P>
It is notable that China has played a positive role in
stabilizing the Asian financial situation at a time when there is
an economic crisis there, Clinton said.
</P>
<P>
The president also appreciated China's role in preventing the
spread of weapons of mass destruction, in combating international
crime and drug trafficking, and in protecting the environment.
</P>
</TEXT>
