<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Pakistan Announces Moratorium on Nuclear Testing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, June 11 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan Thursday announced a
unilateral moratorium on nuclear testing two weeks after the
country carried out its own nuclear tests in response to such
tests by neighboring rival India.
</P>
<P>
The Pakistani government, which repeatedly stated that it does
not wish to enter into an arms race with India, is making active
efforts to ensure avoidance of conflict and promote nuclear and
conventional restraint and stabilization measures between the two
countries, the Foreign Office said in a press statement Thursday
evening.
</P>
<P>
"It is in this context that the government of Pakistan has
decided to announce a unilateral moratorium on nuclear testing,"
it said.
</P>
<P>
"We are ready to engage constructively with India and other
members of the international community to formalize this
arrangement," it said.
</P>
<P>
"In the first instance, we are ready to arrive at a no-nuclear
test agreement with India, as an important confidence building
measure at the regional level," it added.
</P>
<P>
"Pakistan expresses the hope that India will reciprocate and
contribute toward creating a conducive regional environment by
taking further effective steps to overcome the security crisis and
promote durable peace and stability in South Asia," it said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
