<DOCNO> XIE19980612.0008 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> APEC Business Travel Card Scheme Trial-Run in HK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 11 (Xinhua) -- A trial-run of the APEC Business
Travel Card Scheme has started here to enhance the mobility of
business travelers within APEC economies, Hong Kong's Immigration
Department announced Thursday.
</P>
<P>
"The APEC (Asia-Pacific Economic Cooperation) Business Travel
Card is in the size of a credit card and valid for five years
(three years for those issued under the trial-run scheme). The
card will enable the holder to make multiple visits of two months
to participating economies without visa," a spokesperson for the
department said.
</P>
<P>
Card holders will also enjoy streamlined immigration clearance
procedure at the control points of participating economies. In
Hong Kong, they will be allowed to use "Hong Kong Residents"
counters, the spokesperson said.
</P>
<P>
Participating in the trial-run of the scheme are Australia,
Chile, the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region, the
Philippines and the Republic of Korea. In the trial-run Hong Kong
will issue a maximum of 2,000 cards.
</P>
<P>
Applications will be accepted only from those who are invited
to apply. Trade-related organizations have been invited to
nominate eligible applicants, who must hold a Hong Kong permanent
identity card and a valid national passport and has never been
convicted of a criminal offense, according to the spokesperson.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
