<DOCNO> XIE19980612.0013 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Italian President Visits Xi'an </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XI'AN, June 11 (Xinhua) -- Governor of northwest China's
Shaanxi Province Cheng Andong met here this evening with visiting
Italian President Oscar Luigi Scalfaro, who arrived here this
morning by plane from Beijing.
</P>
<P>
Noting that both China and Italy are countries with ancient
civilization, Cheng said that many Italian experiences in
protecting historical cities are worth learning, since Xi'an and
Rome are both world-renowned ancient cities.
</P>
<P>
Cheng expressed his appreciation for the Italian government's
support for China in its efforts to protect historical and
cultural relics, and said that he looked forward to more bilateral
cooperation in culture and economy.
</P>
<P>
Scalfaro said that he was glad to witness China's history and
prosperity on his trip.
</P>
<P>
Scalfaro and his party visited the provincial history museum
and a center for Sino-Italian cooperation in the protection and
renovation of historical and cultural relics, where he met with
dozens of experts from both sides and praised their work.
</P>
<P>
He said that the work being done by these experts once again
proved that there were links between the two peoples in ancient
times, and that such cooperation is a good way to enhance their
friendship and mutual understanding.
</P>
<P>
The Italian visitors are scheduled to leave here for Shanghai
tomorrow. 
</P>
</TEXT>
