<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Li Lanqing Calls for Study of Deng Xiaoping's Theory on Education </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 11 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Vice-Premier Li Lanqing
said here today that leading officials and all the people in the
educational field should take the study of Deng Xiaoping's theory
on education as an urgent task.
</P>
<P>
Attending a seminar on the study of Deng's theory on education,
which was held at the Great Hall of the People in Beijing, Li
urged leading officials at various levels to make a conscientious
study of Deng's theory, carry out the strategy of revitalizing the
nation with science and education, and do a better job of
educational reform and development.
</P>
<P>
Li, also a Standing Committee member of the Political Bureau of
the Communist Party of China (CPC) Central Committee, noted that
Deng's theory on education is a key component of Deng Xiaoping
Theory and a guideline for the country's socialist educational
task in the new period.
</P>
<P>
Deng gave great attention to education and took education and
scientific and technological development as strategic matters
concerning China's modernization and the fate of socialism
in China, Li said.
</P>
<P>
Guided by Deng Xiaoping's theory on education, China's
educational reform has been well under way over the past two
decades, and fast-developing education has made remarkable
contributions to the growth of the national economy, scientific and
technological advancement and social progress, the vice-premier said.
</P>
<P>
Li stressed that the study of Deng Xiaoping's theory on
education must be done in line with the practical and effective
implementation of the theory. 
</P>
</TEXT>
