<HEADLINE> Chongqing, Shanghai Seek Economic Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHONGQING, June 11 (Xinhua) -- Closer cooperation between the
municipalities of Shanghai and Chongqing will not only boost their
economic growth, but also be vital to the development of China's
central and western regions as well as the areas along the Yangtze
River, said the two municipalities' leaders.
</P>
<P>
Huang Ju, member of the Political Bureau of the Central
Committee of the Communist Party of China (CPC) and secretary of
the CPC Shanghai Municipal Committee, and Shanghai Mayor Xu
Kuangdi led a delegation to Chongqing on June 9-11, and exchanged
views with the leaders of Chongqing on how to further economic
cooperation each other.
</P>
<P>
Both sides agreed that mutual supplement of advantages of
Shanghai and Chongqing will help boost the development and opening
of cities along the Yangtze River, and accelerate the optimization
of the essential factors of production and the process of economic
integration.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that Shanghai has now more than 120 enterprises
funded by Chongqing, while it has launched nearly 100
cooperation projects in Chongqing.
</P>
<P>
After discussion, they decided to increase cooperation in four
aspects, namely, the development of high-tech products, the
establishment of transregional large enterprises, infrastructural
construction, and market fostering. 
</P>
</TEXT>
