<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> NPC Vice-chairman Donates 1,000 Yuan to China's Anti-Drug Cause </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 11 (Xinhua) -- Wang Guangying, Vice-chairman of
the Standing Committee of the National People's Congress (NPC),
donated 1,000 yuan to China's anti-drug campaign here today at the
ongoing national anti-drug exhibition.
</P>
<P>
Standing in front of the memorial to the anti-drug martyrs in
the exhibition hall, Wang listened to the heroic deeds of the
martyrs and shed tears.
</P>
<P>
He demanded the staff of the exhibition buy a wreath and
present it in honor of the martyrs.
</P>
<P>
"I was deeply moved by the exhibition," said Zou Jiahua,
another vice-chairman of the Standing Committee of the NPC, adding
that China should conduct a ``harsh and long-term battle against
drugs."
</P>
<P>
He suggested that the publicity of the anti-drug campaign be
further intensified so as to make more ordinary people know about
the danger of drugs.
</P>
<P>
All staff members of the anti-drug division of the Beijing
Municipal Public Security Bureau laid a wreath in front of
the memorial to the anti-drug martyrs this morning, and solemnly
declared that they would continue the unfinished work
of the martyrs and strike hard against drug crimes. 
</P>
</TEXT>
