<HEADLINE> Italy Ties Chile 1-1 at Halftime </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BORDEAUX, France, June 11 (Xinhua) -- Italy tied with Chile 1-1 at
halftime in their Group B opener in the soccer World Cup finals here
on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Christian Vieri opened the scoring for Italy in the 10th minute,
blasting the ball home past Chilean goalkeeper Nelson Tapia from the
edge of the penalty area on a Roberto Baggio pass.
</P>
<P>
Chile equalized in the last minute of the first half when striker
Marcelo Salas chipped the ball into the net in blank range.
