<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Software Exports Have Big Chance to Develop: Report </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, June 11 (Xinhua) -- Romania's software industry is
one of the first fields having big chances to develop besides
agriculture, tourism and mineral waters, the Romanian national
news agency Rompres reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Romania exports at the moment software amounting to about 10
million U.S. dollars annually as against an estimated 1 billion
dollars, namely, a 100 times larger, said Rompres.
</P>
<P>
"Romania can export software worth about 1 billion dollars
annually, reads Romanian theoretical reckonings based on the human
potential existing at a national level. And foreign analysts see
Romania as a possible leader of the information technology
market," said Florin Talpes, the General Manager of Softwin
Company.
</P>
<P>
The informatics expert ratio for every thousand inhabitants in
Romania is seven times larger than in India, a world-famous
software exporter. Romania counts 5,000 informatics graduates a
year. This level is five times smaller than that in India, whose
population is 35 times larger, Rompres said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
