<HEADLINE> 2 Israeli-allied Militiamen Killed in South </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIRUT, June 11 (Xinhua) -- Two Israeli-allied South Lebanese
Army (SLA) members were killed and at least three others wounded
in separate attacks by Lebanese anti-Israeli guerrillas in south
Lebanon Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The Voice of the People radio said a roadside bomb killed an
SLA and injured three others when an SLA patrol passed by in
Jezzine, just north of the Israeli occupied south Lebanon enclave.
</P>
<P>
The Iranian-backed Hezbollah, or Party of God, claimed the
responsibility for the attack, the radio added.
</P>
<P>
Hours before, another SLA member had been killed in a mortar
attack launched by Hezbollah guerrillas on an SLA post also in
Jezzine. Hezbollah said in a statement that the attack also
wounded others.
</P>
<P>
In retaliation for Hezbollah's attack, Israeli warplanes staged
a raid on the guerrilla stronghold in the Iqlim Toufah area, near
Jezzine.
</P>
<P>
Israel has been occupying a 1,200-square-kilometer border strip
in south Lebanon in alliance with its proxy SLA since 1985 to
allegedly protect its north from Lebanese guerrilla attack. Since
then, Israeli troops have met a strong anti-occupation movement
spearheaded by Hezbollah. 
</P>
</TEXT>
