<HEADLINE> Khamenei Calls for Unity to Deal With "Main </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, June 11 (Xinhua) -- Iranian supreme leader Ayatollah
Ali Khamenei on Thursday strongly called for unity of the nation
to deal with the "main enemies" of the Islamic revolution.
</P>
<P>
Khamenei issued the call at a speech to a large crowd during
his inspection tour in Amol, northern province of Mazadaran,
according to the Iranian official news agency IRNA.
</P>
<P>
He said that unity and following the guidance of Islam and holy
Koran are the two principles for the progressive process of the
Islamic revolution.
</P>
<P>
Khamenei made the call at a time when the Iranian powerful
conservatives launched new offensives against the moderate
government by putting Tehran Mayor Gholamhussein Karbaschi on
open trial and demanding an impeachment of Interior Minister
Abdollah Nouri.
</P>
<P>
The conservative judiciary started the trial on Karbaschi
on Sunday, but the accused rejected all charges leveled against
him.
</P>
<P>
On Wednesday, 31 Majlis (parliament) deputies proposed a motion
to impeach Nouri. They said in the motion that "continuation of
Nouri's service at the post of interior minister is detrimental
to tranquillity and stability of the country."
</P>
<P>
Iranian President Mohammad Khatami on Wednesday expressed
welcome to the challenges, saying that the process of impeachment
would help bring about the necessary transparency in the
government's stance.
</P>
<P>
"I believe that Nouri has the necessary capability to
elaborate on the stance and issues related to the Interior
Ministry," he said.
</P>
<P>
Khamenei made no comment on the factional struggles, saying
that the enemies of the Islamic revolution are trying in vain to
make the nation forget the main enemies and sow discord among the
people.
</P>
<P>
He said that an independent and free nation is one that is
capable of standing on its own feet and tread the right path with
unity, adding that the Iranian nation has done so in the past 19
years and has made great achievements.
</P>
<P>
The Iranian leader reminded the people of the will of the late
Iranian supreme leader Ayatollah Musavi Khomeini who called on
the nation to resort to Islam and solidarity and not to neglect
the enemy.
</P>
<P>
Khamenei said that the enemy does not always penetrate through
geographical borders, sometimes it may infiltrate through the
cultural borders, something which requires more care on the part
of the people to deal with it. 
</P>
</TEXT>
