<HEADLINE> UN Envoy Promises to Stay on in Angola </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, June 11 (Xinhua) -- United Nations Special Envoy to
Angola, Blondin Beye, said here Thursday that he would stay on in
Angola until final peace is crystalized in the country.
</P>
<P>
Speaking on returning here from his U.N. Security Council
meeting on Angola, Beye said that peace here needs a mediator,
but whether his mission could be completed hinges on the
resumption of trust by both sides of the peace process.
</P>
<P>
Beye said he would continue his southern African tour to
solicit support for the peace effort, so as to end the four-year
long peace process in Angola as soon as possible.
</P>
<P>
The peace process in Angola is experiencing a critical period
as militiamen of the National Union for the Total Independence of
Angola (UNITA) are still carrying out sabotage activities in
parts of the country, and the UNITA leaders refuse to hand out
the four sensitive areas to the government. 
</P>
