<HEADLINE> Italy Ties Chile 2-2 in Group B </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BORDEAUX, France, June 11 (Xinhua) -- Italy tied with Chile 2-2 in
their Group B opener in the soccer World Cup finals here on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Christian Vieri put Italy ahead in the 10th minute, blasting the
ball home past Chilean goalkeeper Nelson Tapia from the edge of the
penalty area on a Roberto Baggio pass.
</P>
<P>
Chile equalized in the last minute of the first half when striker
Salas shot in blank range.
</P>
<P>
Salas netted again five minutes into the second half with a header
over Italian keeper Gianluca Pagliuca, sending the Chilean fans among
the 31,800 spectators at the Stade Lescure into ecstasy.
</P>
<P>
Italy levelled the score in the 85th minute through Baggio, who
converted a penalty kick awarded controversially after Chile's Ronaldo
Fuentes handed the ball in the area.
</P>
<P>
Referee Lucian Bouchardeau of Nigeria handed out five yellow cards
in the heavily-contested match, including those to Italians Angelo Di
Livio and Fabio Cannavaro.
</P>
<P>
Chile's Nelson Parraguez, Clarence Acuna and Francisco Rojas were
also warned. 
</P>
</TEXT>
