<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Baggio Saves Italy With Late Goal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
BORDEAUX, June 11 (Xinhua) -- Roberto Boggio, who entered the
World Cup finals at the last minutes, pulled Italy back from the
brink of defeat with a penalty kick late in the match against Chile.
</P>
<P>
The Italian team, who was trademarked with slow warm-up in major
international tournaments, were badly off form in the opening match
of Group B which also includes Cameroon and Austria.
</P>
<P>
The Chilean team, led by deadly duo Ivan Zamorano and Marcelo
Salas, showed that they were the better prepared team in the first
20 minutes of the match.
</P>
<P>
The Chilean team took control of the midfield with smooth
combinations while the Italian team appeared sluggish.
</P>
<P>
But it was the Italians who opened the scoring. Captain Paolo
Maldini launched a quick counter-attack with an accurate long-range
pass and Christian Vieri beat the Chilean goal-keeper Tapia with a
left-foot shot.
</P>
<P>
The Italians played a little bit better in the remaining time of
the first half. But the Chilean team came back into the match and
forced a corner in the injury time. Salas slamed home a rebound to
level the score 1-1.
</P>
<P>
In the second half, the Chileans played a more aggressive and
effective game with their quick and accurate pass. Salas scored
again on a head pass from Zamorano.
</P>
<P>
The Chileans seemed very likely to win the match as the match
approaching to its end. But Baggio saved the Italian team as his
pass hit the hand of Chilean defender Ronald Fuentes at the 84th
minute. The Nigerian refree Lucien Bouchardear awarded the penalty
kick to Italy.
</P>
<P>
Baggio, who missed a penalty shot four years ago in the final of
the World Cup in the United States, scored from the spot with a low
right-foot shot.
</P>
<P>
The Italian team missed their ace striker Alessandro Del Piero
who is still not one hundred percent fit.
</P>
<P>
Later on Thursday, Cameroon and Austria will play the other
Group B match at Toulouse. 
</P>
</TEXT>
