<HEADLINE> WB to Loan Ethiopia $60M for Agriculture </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, June 11 (Xinhua) -- The World Bank has approved a
60-million-U.S.-Dollar credit to support agricultural research
and training in Ethiopia.
</P>
<P>
A news release available here Thursday said that the project
will help promote economic growth, reduce poverty, protect the
environment, and will support the effort to attain food security.
</P>
<P>
The release issued by the Africa Regional Office of the World
Bank said that the project will improve or establish regional
research centers which will respond to the agricultural needs
determined by local farmers.
</P>
