<HEADLINE> Arafat to Visit Italy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, June 11 (Xinhua) -- Palestinian leader Yasser Arafat
is to visit Italy on Friday to discuss with Italian leaders the
latest efforts in reviving the deadlocked peace process with
Israel.
</P>
<P>
"Chairman Arafat will discuss with the Italian leaders the ways
of getting the peace process out of its dangerous impasse and he
will also meet with Pope John Paul II at the Vatican to discuss
with him the Israeli violations of Palestinian holy sites," an
official close to Arafat told Xinhua.
</P>
<P>
During his stay in Italy, Arafat will also be presented with a
prize for his efforts to bring about peace in the region, the
official said on customary condition of anonymity.
</P>
<P>
He added that a joint Palestinian-Italian ministerial committee
will meet in Rome to discuss arrangements for the Bethlehem 2000
celebrations, during which millions of Christian pilgrims are
expected to visit the holy site of Jesus' birth.
</P>
<P>
The official also confirmed that Arafat postponed his scheduled
visit to Egypt on Thursday due to "technical reasons."
</P>
<P>
On Thursday evening before his departure for Rome, Arafat will
chair the weekly meeting of the Palestinian leadership in Gaza to
discuss the crisis of the peace process, the Israeli government's
evasion of the signed agreements and its increasing settlement
activities on Palestinian lands.
</P>
<P>
During the weekly meeting, the leadership will also discuss
the results of Arafat's latest tour to the Arab nations to rally
support for holding an Arab summit.
</P>
<P>
The Palestinian leadership consists of members of the Executive
Committee of the Palestinian Liberation Organization and ministers
of the Palestinian National Authority. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
