<HEADLINE> Moldovan Vice-Premier on Relations with Russia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, June 11 (Xinhua) -- The relations of Moldova with
Russia are one of the priorities of the economic policy, conducted
by the new government of Moldova, Vice-Premier, the Minister of
Economics and Reforms, Ion Sturza said Thursday in an interview
with the Moscow NTV television canal on Chisinau.
</P>
<P>
Over the first four months of this year, he said, more than 60
percent of all Moldovan export volumes is realized on the Russia's
market and the share of this country in the total foreign trade of
the Republic exceeds 40 percent.
</P>
<P>
"There are certain difficulties in the relations of Moldova and
Russia, generated by a financial, production crisis, which
undoubtedly influences the whole process of commodities turnover
between them," Ion Sturza said, adding "That is why Moldova has
been actively looking for its place in other countries of the
world."  
</P>
</TEXT>
