<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Car-Truck Collision Claims 8 Lives in S. Africa </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, June 11 (Xinhua) -- Eight people were killed
instantly and four others seriously injured when a car and a
truck collided near Greytown in eastern Kwazulu-Natal, on
Thursday afternoon, South African Press Association reported.
</P>
<P>
The car apparently overtook another vehicle and crashed into
the oncoming truck. The car overturned and the driver of the car
was among the dead.
</P>
<P>
Two of the injured were reportedly in a critical condition.
</P>
</TEXT>
