<HEADLINE> Dumpling Culture Festival Held in Xi'an </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XI'AN, June 12 (Xinhua) -- A jiaozi (dumpling) culture festival
and jiaozi culture seminar were launched in Xi'an, capital
of northwest China's Shaanxi Province, today.
</P>
<P>
Jiaozi, which is made from meat and vegetable stuffing with
dough wrapper, has been a kind of symbolic traditional Chinese
food and popular among the Chinese with its unique flavor.
</P>
<P>
In Xi'an City, the Defachang Jiaozi Restaurant, an old name in
jiaozi business, has developed a special jiaozi banquet in which
100 kinds of jiaozi with different stuffings are available for
gourmets.
</P>
<P>
At present, the jiaozi banquet has become a special and major
type of delicacy for domestic and foreign guests to the ancient
city of Xi'an.
</P>
<P>
Scholars on folk culture from Germany, Norway, Japan and
other countries are invited to attend the jiaozi festival and
have cultural exchanges. 
</P>
</TEXT>
