<HEADLINE> HK External Trade Shrinks in April </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 12 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong's re-exports decreased
by 3.8 percent in April 1998 over a year earlier to 100.5 billion
HK dollars (12.9 billion U.S. dollars), the Census and Statistics
Department said on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The value of domestic exports lost 6 percent to 15.5 billion HK
dollars (2 billion U.S. dollars) while the value of imports
dropped by 4.2 percent to 133.2 billion HK dollars (17.1 billion
U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
For the first four months of 1998, the value of re-exports,
domestic exports and imports dropped 1 percent, 7 percent and 4.9
percent respectively from the same period last year, according to
the department. 
</P>
