<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Australian Dollar Closes Almost Steady </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, June 12 (Xinhua) -- The Australian dollar clawed its
way above the key 59 U.S. cent level Friday to close almost
steady.
</P>
<P>
But foreign exchange dealers said that by no means was the
local currency out of the wood.
</P>
<P>
"There is little on the immediate horizon to lighten the heavy
baggage that the Australian dollar is carrying at present," the
Commonwealth Bank of Australia's Michael Blythe said.
</P>
<P>
At the close in Sydney the Australian dollar was trading at
59.17 U.S. cents from 59.18 U.S. cents at Thursday night's close.
</P>
<P>
A trader said the Australian dollar was also helped by
unsupported rumors that a mining company was buying Australian
dollars to make a takeover bid for Australia's leading company BHP
Co. Ltd. and also by purchase of the Australian dollar ahead of
Monday's float of Australia's insurance giant AMP.
</P>
<P>
In a commotion-filled week the battered domestic unit plumbed
to lows last seen in the "banana republic" days of 1986 and fell
to its lowest ever closing level.
</P>
<P>
On June 10 the Australian dollar dropped to as low as 58.09
U.S. cents, the lowest level reached since July 28, 1986, when it
hit a record post-float low of 57.1 U.S. cents.
</P>
<P>
"The risks on the currency front remain skewed to the downside
reflecting the Australian dollar's role as a barometer of
attitudes toward Asia, continued pressure on the Japanese yen,
concerns about trends in the current account deficit and commodity
prices and general negative market sentiment," Blythe said.
</P>
<P>
He said the downside risks for the battered currency had been
heightened by renewed concerns over the outlook for Asia which has
been reflected in fresh weakness in Asian equity markets over the
past week.
</P>
<P>
On the cross rates Friday, the Australian dollar was trading at
85.16 Japanese yen from 83.88 yen at Thursday night's close.
</P>
<P>
It was also trading at 1.069 German marks from 1.0636 marks, at
0.3627 British pounds from 0.3634 pounds and 1.1787 New Zealand
dollars from 1.1792. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
