<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Poverty to Be Reduced through Macroeconomic Policies </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, June 12 (Xinhua) -- The Pakistani government will
reduce poverty through combination of macroeconomic policies, high
economic growth and strengthened links and coordination among key
areas.
</P>
<P>
According to the Annual Development Plan for 1998-99, the first
year of the Ninth Five-Year Plan, released here Friday, the
government will focus its attention more on the development of the
social sectors.
</P>
<P>
Efforts will be made to further improve social development,
increase budgetary allocations for social development and boost
inter-governmental coordination and collaboration.
</P>
<P>
Under the plan, the government has made an overall increase of
18 percent in allocations for the vital Social Action Program
(SAP) for the new fiscal year (July 1-June 30).
</P>
<P>
The total size of allocations for SAP is estimated at 77.112
billion rupees (about 17.5 million U.S. dollars), a rise of 18
percent over that in the outgoing fiscal year.
</P>
<P>
For the next fiscal year the SAP will mainly focus on
integrating social sector policies, mitigating institutional
rigidity and overcoming procedural inadequacies and consolidating
and expanding the services and programs launched and benefits
achieved during the last several years.
</P>
<P>
According to the Annual Development Plan, the government will
play a catalyst role in policies and programs of poverty
alleviation.
</P>
<P>
The government during the Ninth Five-Year Plan (1998-2003)
period will reinforce the process of sustained and integrated
economic growth and social development toward the enhancement of
the quality of life for all people.
</P>
<P>
The government's social agenda during the next five years will
be based on the three core areas of poverty alleviation,
employment expansion and social integration. 
</P>
</TEXT>
