<HEADLINE> Students To Serve Rural Residents </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 12 (Xinhua) -- Over 500,000 Chinese college and
middle school students will participate in various activities in
rural areas during the summer vacation from early July to middle
Augest.
</P>
<P>
This was revealed at today's teleconference covering
arrangement for the program, which was sponsored by the Ministry
of Education and relevant departments.
</P>
<P>
The students will assist in efforts to reduce illiteracy,
present theatrical performances for farmers, promote science and
technology, offer advice on rural industrial developments and
provide medical services to rural people.
</P>
<P>
Hu Chunhua, member of the Secretariat of the Communist Youth
League Central Committee, said that serving in rural areas will
enable students to learn more about society and improve their
personal quality. 
</P>
</TEXT>
