<HEADLINE> High-Tech Training for Senior Military Officers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGSHA, June 12 (Xinhua) -- A high-tech training class for
senior military officers closed today at the National Defense
Science and Technology University in Changsha, capital of central
China's Hunan Province.
</P>
<P>
Dozens of senior officers from various branches of the armed
forces attended the two month course covering the
characteristics, patterns and tactics of warfare in a high-tech
environment.
</P>
<P>
The goal of the program was to carry out the strategic
principle of the Central Military Commission in the new period in
order to raise the quality of leading officers and promote further
modernization of the Chinese army, according to military sources.
</P>
<P>
The training class covered subjects such as basic aspects of
high technology, electronic warfare and information war and
precise guiding technology. 
</P>
</TEXT>
