<BODY>
<HEADLINE> HK Marks 60th Birthday of China Defense League </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 12 (Xinhua) -- More than 200 people gathered at
a reception here Friday in commemoration of the 60th anniversary
of the founding of the China Defense League by Soong Ching Ling.
</P>
<P>
The league is the predecessor of the China Welfare Institute, a
non-governmental organization engaged in medical, social and
educational work for the Chinese people and in particular for
women and children.
</P>
<P>
Founded by Soong Ching Ling in Hong Kong on June 14, 1938, the
China Defense League was aimed at collecting large amounts of
medical and material supplies from overseas to help China in the
War of Resistance Against Japan (1937-1945).
</P>
<P>
The relief organization also undertook the task of reporting to
the outside world the true situation of struggle in China. Based
in Hong Kong for three years, it received full support from Hong
Kong compatriots, overseas Chinese and many foreign friends.
</P>
<P>
At Friday's reception, Huang Hua, chairman of the
Shanghai-based China Welfare Institute, spoke highly of the
tradition of patriotism of the Chinese people in Hong Kong and
their deep concern for the motherland.
</P>
<P>
Chief Executive of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region
Tung Chee Hwa was present at the gathering, which was attended by
more than 200 representatives of all sectors from Beijing,
Shanghai and Hong Kong. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
