<HEADLINE> Pakistan's Manufacturing to Grow by 7.2 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, June 12 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan has set an overall
growth rate target of 7.2 percent for 1998-1999 in the
manufacturing sector with 6.5 percent in large-scale industries
and 8.4 percent in small ones.
</P>
<P>
Under the Annual Plan 1998-99 issued here Friday afternoon, an
allocation of 597 million rupees (about 14 million U.S. dollars)
has been proposed for the manufacturing sector for the year
1998-99 as compared with the estimated expenditure of 650.69
million rupees (14.8 million dollars) during 1997-1998.
</P>
<P>
According to the economic survey 1997-1998 issued on Wednesday,
the country's manufacturing sector grew by 7 percent during
1997-1998 while growth of large-scale manufacturing recovered from
last year's negative 2.3 percent to 6.2 percent. However,
small-scale manufacturing maintained its previous growth of 8.4
percent. 
</P>
