<HEADLINE> China Repairs 990-Year-Old Islamic Building </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, June 12 (Xinhua) -- The 990-year-old Qingjing Mosque,
China's oldest Islamic building, is being repaired in Quanzhou City
in east China's Fujian Province.
</P>
<P>
The mosque, built in 1009 during the Song Dynasty (960-1279) in
Quanzhou port, was the starting port of the "Marine Silk Road", a
famous ancient trade channel between the east and the west.
</P>
<P>
According to historic records, many Islam believers from
Arabic countries were living and doing business in the city and
had religious service in the mosque.
</P>
<P>
The repairs on the collapsed meeting room, exhibition hall,
guest room, and shower room is expected to be completed by the end
of the year. And the mosque's walls and leading hall for religious
service will be rebuilt next year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
