<DOCNO> XIE19980612.0141 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Maintains Steady Growth in Overseas Tourists </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 12 (Xinhua) -- Overseas tourists to China
amounted to 5.758 million in April, a year-on-year rise of 22.4
percent, according to the latest statistics from the China
National Tourism Administration.
</P>
<P>
Among them, foreign tourists were 630,000, down by 2 percent,
while visitors from Hong Kong and Macao were 4.918 million, up
28.1 percent.
</P>
<P>
Affected by the Asian financial crisis, people from the
Republic of Korea and Thailand dropped by a big margin, and those
from Japan, Malaysia, and Singapore went down slightly.
</P>
<P>
The number of tourists from other continents than Asia
increased by varying degrees, with some countries reporting
double-digit growth. Australia has registered a 50.3 percent rise.
</P>
<P>
During the period, China earned 1.136 billion US dollars in
overseas tourism, up 12.4 percent from the corresponding 1997
period.
</P>
<P>
A little more than 20 million overseas tourists came to China
in the first four months of the year, an increase of 13.7 percent,
and brought about nearly 4 billion US dollars, up 10.7 percent.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
