<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> HK First Legislative Council to Meet on July 2 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 12 (Xinhua) -- Chief Executive Tung Chee Hwa of
the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (SAR) has set
July 2, 1998, as the commencement date of the first ordinary
session of the first Legislative Council of the SAR.
</P>
<P>
A government spokesman said the Legislative Council (LegCo)
will hold the first meeting at 3:30 p.m. on July 2.
</P>
<P>
The term of office of the first Legislative Council commences
on July 1, 1998 and lasts for two years.
</P>
<P>
In view of the tightly scheduled activities for the SAR first
anniversary celebration of July 1 and the past practice that the
commencement of a LegCo session and the first LegCo meeting fell
on the same day, the chief executive has decided to fix the
commencement date of the first LegCo session on July 2, the
spokesman added.
</P>
<P>
The first Legislative Council of the SAR was elected on May
24.  
</P>
</TEXT>
