<HEADLINE> First State Travel Agency Turned into Stock Company </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, June 12 (Xinhua) -- The first state-owned travel
agency, the Guangzhilu International Travel Agency Co. Ltd., in
this capital of south China's Guangdong Province, has been turned
into a share-holding company today.
</P>
<P>
It was formerly the city's largest state tourism company and,
after the transformation, the newly-founded company now has 38
million yuan (4.58 million US dollars) in registered capital.
</P>
<P>
The major components of the share-holders include 41 percent of
state-controlled stocks, and 36.9 percent of staff-held shares,
with all 300-odd workers buying stocks worth more than 30,000 yuan
(3,600 US dollars) on average. So, managers and workers and
staffers will share profits and losses.
</P>
<P>
The company also opened a tourism culture square today for
photo exhibitions, film shows, art performances and sale of local
products, as well as on-the-spot consulting activities. 
</P>
</TEXT>
