<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Stocks Rebound Slightly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 12 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong stocks rebounded a
slight 29.37 points, or 0.37 percent, to close at 7,915 Friday.
</P>
<P>
The market's turnover was 5,987 million HK dollars (767.56
million U.S. dollars), 764 million HK dollars (97.95 million
U.S. dollars) less than that of Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The key Hang Seng Index lost 136.58 points, or 1.73 percent, to
open at 7,749.49 Friday morning. It gained 30.90 points, or 0.39
percent, to close at 7,916.97 at midday.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong shares had dropped some 700 points in three straight
days since Tuesday due to the impact of the weakness of the
Japanese yen and came to a post-crisis record low Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The HSI fell 93.30 points, or 1.17 percent, to close at
7,886.07 Thursday.  
</P>
</TEXT>
