<DOCNO> XIE19980612.0145 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hong Kong SAR to Celebrate First Birthday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 12 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong will organize a
variety of activities ranging from hoisting of flags to carnivals
in celebration of the first anniversary of the establishment of
the Special Administrative Region (SAR), the government announced
here Friday.
</P>
<P>
David Lan, Secretary for Home Affairs, told a press conference
Friday that on the morning of July 1, Chief Executive Tung Chee
Hwa will officiate at a flag-raising ceremony near the
six-meter-high bauhinia sculpture at the waterfront of the
Victoria Harbor.
</P>
<P>
The glistening, gold-plated sculpture, entitled "Forever
Blooming Bauhinia", was a gift from the Central People's
government to mark the founding of the SAR on July 1, 1997.
</P>
<P>
This year, a large-scale performance will be staged at the
12,500-seat Hung Hom Coliseum, where musicians from Japan, Europe
and the United States will join hands with local artists.
</P>
<P>
Lan said: "We want to show to the world that Hong Kong is a
metropolis full of vitality, and Hong Kong is where the Chinese
and Western cultures meet."
</P>
<P>
In the evening, the SAR government will host a banquet for
1,000 distinguished guests.
</P>
<P>
A grand carnival will be held at the Happy Valley Race Course
in Hong Kong on July 1, open free to all Hong Kong people.
</P>
<P>
Lan said that there will be about 60 non-government activities
of celebration around July 1, such as football tournament,
Cantonese opera show, Chinese acrobatic show and bus parade.
</P>
<P>
"The one-year birthday is very important according to the
Chinese custom. The celebration this year will be simple and
solemn," he said.
</P>
<P>
He said the concepts of "Hong Kong people ruling Hong Kong" and
"a high degree of autonomy" all came to reality over the past
year. "Hong Kong has performed well in the unfavorable external
environment. Things are moving in the right direction," he added.
</P>
<P>
The estimated spending for the first anniversary will exceed 10
million HK dollars (1.28 million U.S. dollars), according to
Lan.  
</P>
</TEXT>
