<HEADLINE> Lesotho's Deputy Premier Sworn in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, June 12 (Xinhua) -- Lesotho's new Deputy Prime
Minister Kelebone Maope was sworn in Friday before King Letsie
III at the Basotho Royal Palace in Maseru, South African Press
Association reported.
</P>
<P>
Maope, who was former foreign minister, also holds the
portfolio of Minister of Agriculture, Cooperatives and Land
Reclamation.
</P>
<P>
Shakhane Mokhehle, the younger brother of former prime
minister Ntsu Mokhehle, was sworn in as Minister of Works and
Transport.
</P>
<P>
These two portfolios were vacant when the majority of the new
cabinet was sworn in last Friday. It is understood that Maope and
Mokhehle at first declined the portfolios on the grounds that
they were not properly consulted by the new Prime Minister,
Pakalitha Mosisili.
</P>
<P>
Their approval came after lengthy negotiations which included
the intervention of the former prime minister.
</P>
<P>
The swearing-in of the two ministers completed the formation
of Lesotho's new cabinet after the May 23 general election.
</P>
</TEXT>
