<HEADLINE> Suzhou Encourages Local Firms Producing Parts for Foreigners </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, June 12 (Xinhua) -- A trade negotiation fair opened
today in Suzhou in east China's Jiangsu province to encourage
local firms to produce parts for foreign companies.
</P>
<P>
More than 150 foreign firms and 1000-plus local ones attended
the fair to negotiate on manufacturing of 1,000 kinds of parts.
</P>
<P>
Suzhou now has more than 5,000 foreign-funded firms in
operation. To decrease costs, these firms want to localize their
parts production. In the meantime, the local firms are willing to
improve their management and join in the international competition
through cooperation with foreign ones.
</P>
<P>
Last year, 300 local firms were engaged in such business and
generated a 2.2 billion yuan of sales volume. The figure is
expected to increase to four billion yuan this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
