<HEADLINE> Guangxi to Sell Power Plant's Property Right to Foreign Investors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANNING, June 12 (Xinhua) -- The Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous
Region in south China is planning to sell one of its power plants'
property right to foreign investors in the form of TOT
(transfer-operate-transfer).
</P>
<P>
This is the first case China has ever officially approved to
transfer the property right of large and medium-sized power
plants to overseas businesses, local government sources said.
</P>
<P>
The A Plant of Guangxi Laibin Power Plant, under Guangxi
Development and Investment Co. Ltd. and with a total installed
capacity of 250,000 kw, began operation in 1989.
</P>
<P>
The move aims at raising money for local infrastructure.
</P>
<P>
A leading group has been set up by the regional goverment to
take care of the transfer and bidding.  
</P>
</TEXT>
