<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 40 Good Citizens Awarded by HK Police </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 12 (Xinhua) -- Man Chi-fung, who through his
alertness helped the police arrest a suspect in connection with a
taxi robbery case, was presented with a good citizen certificate
here Friday.
</P>
<P>
The 29-year-old Man also won a cash prize of 3,000 HK dollars
(385 U.S. dollars) from the police at the Good Citizen Award
presentation ceremony Friday afternoon.
</P>
<P>
Thirty-nine other civic-minded Hong Kong citizens, comprising
37 men and two women aged from 13 to 50, were also awarded.
</P>
<P>
The youngest award recipient, 13-year-old Suen Chak-fan, saw a
man stealing money from a cash register in a stationery shop on
September 6 last year. The man gave him some money and told him
not to say anything before leaving the shop.
</P>
<P>
When the shop proprietor returned, Suen informed her of the
incident. Realizing that 580 HK dollars (74 U.S. dollars) had
been missing from the cash register, she reported the case to a
police officer outside the shop. The man was arrested in the
vicinity with the help of Suen.
</P>
<P>
The award presentation ceremony, held twice a year, was
organized by the Hong Kong Police with sponsorship from the Hong
Kong General Chamber of Commerce.
</P>
<P>
Almon Poon Chin-hung, member of the government's Fight Crime
Committee, praised the 40 persons for displaying outstanding
courage, alertness and resourcefulness.
</P>
<P>
Since the Good Citizen Award Scheme was launched in 1973, 2,664
people have been presented with the award. Poon said: "This shows
the police have obtained extensive support and cooperation from
the public in maintaining law and order in Hong Kong," where the
crime rate is among the world's lowest.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
