<HEADLINE> Kuala Lumpur Stocks Close Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, June 12 (Xinhua) -- Share prices on the Kuala
Lumpur Stock Exchange closed lower Friday in thin trading due to
selling activities sparked by the continuous fall of the Japanese
yen against the U.S. dollar.
</P>
<P>
At the close, the 100-quality stock Composite Index was down
10.63 points to 472.37, the all-share Emas Index shed 2.33 points
to 122.02, the Industrial Index fell 11.62 points to 950.35 and
the Second Board Index eased 0.28 points to 106.36.
</P>
<P>
Losers led gainers by 376 to 167, while 209 counters were
unchanged and 168 untraded.
</P>
<P>
The day's turnover eased to 119.644 million shares valued at
268.206 million ringgit (66.883 million U.S. dollars) from 129.984
million shares valued at 296.947 million ringgit (74.051 million
dollars) Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Turnover on the main board slipped to 113.470 million shares
valued at 259.507 million ringgit (64.714 million dollars) from
Thursday's 122.449 million shares worth 286.603 million ringgit
(71.472 million dollars).
</P>
<P>
On the second board, turnover was at 6.174 million shares worth
8.699 million ringgit (2.169 million dollars) from 7.535 million
shares valued at 10.344 million ringgit (2.579 million dollars)
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Off-market deals rose to 12.783 million shares worth 66.664
million ringgit (16.624 million dollars) from Thursday's 8.508
million shares valued at 20.426 million ringgit (5.093 million
dollars).
</P>
<P>
On a sectoral basis, consumer products accounted for 3.529
million shares traded on the main board, industrial products
6.167 million shares, construction 9.488 million shares,
trading/services 47.258 million shares, infrastructure 1.026
million shares, finance 23.786 million shares, hotels 209,000,
properties 11.549 million shares, plantation 2.920 million shares,
mining 425,000 shares, trusts 74,000 shares, closed/fund 108,000
shares and loans 6.931 million shares. 
</P>
