<HEADLINE> Fresh Cholera Outbreak Kills 33 in Uganda </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, June 12 (Xinhua) -- As many as 33 people have died
and 460 cases were reported as a fresh outbreak of cholera
gripped northern Uganda over the last 10 days, bringing the
national toll up to 1,550 deaths and 37,896 cases since November
1997.
</P>
<P>
A New Vision report Friday listed five of the country's
districts as the most affected including Aura in the north,
Kabarole in the west.
</P>
<P>
Charles Mugero, a member of the national cholera task
force, said that over 140 cholera patients have been reported in
Aura alone.
</P>
<P>
"There is an upsurge in the number of cholera cases. In Arua,
140 new cases were recorded this week," he said, adding that a
team is moving to the area.
</P>
<P>
Health experts have been dispatched to assess the situation
there and provide most needed drugs to the patients.
</P>
<P>
So far there has been no death reported in the capital Kampala
city despite eight cases of the epidemic recorded.  
</P>
</TEXT>
