<HEADLINE> China Construction Bank Backs Key Projects </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 12 (Xinhua) -- The China Construction Bank (CCB),
one of the four biggest state-owned commercial banks in China, is
reported to have acted as an agent of the State Development Bank
(SDB) to handle more than 310 billion yuan in policy loans for the
nation's key projects.
</P>
<P>
The amount accounts for 75 percent of the total loans the SDB
has extended since it was established in 1994.
</P>
<P>
So far, the CCB has taken advantage of its banking network
across the nation to help complete more than 1,000 such key
projects.
</P>
<P>
It also became a major fund provider for the SDB, having
subscribed a total of 54.5 billion yuan in SDB financial bonds by
the end of 1997. It promises to purchase another 12 billion yuan
in such bonds this year.
</P>
<P>
Formerly the nation's leading lender for the basic industries
and key projects, the CCB turned into the leading agent bank for
the SDB's policy-oriented lending business from 1994.
</P>
<P>
China decided to intensify the input into the fixed asset to
push up the economic growth to eight percent this year. As a
result, the SDB has revised its annual lending plan for 1998,
expanding the credit quota from 97.3 billion yuan to the current
120 billion yuan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
