<HEADLINE> Iraq Urges Sympathizers to Help Lift Sanctions </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BAGHDAD, June 12 (Xinhua) -- Iraq on Friday called on
international and humanitarian organizations and figures
sympathetic to Iraq to intensify efforts for the lifting of the
seven-year-old U.N. sanctions.
</P>
<P>
An Iraqi Foreign Ministry spokesman made this call in a
statement to the Iraqi News Agency to clarify Baghdad's decision
to resist any future assistance subsumed under humanitarian aid.
</P>
<P>
An announcement made after a cabinet session June 6 said Iraqi
government had accepted humanitarian donations in the belief that
they would make it easier for those parties sympathetic to Iraq
to remain in touch with Iraq's attempts to bring its cause in
focus.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said irrespective of their amounts, such
donations offered by sympathetic friends were not the sure remedy
for relieving the suffering of 22 million Iraqis under the
sanctions.
</P>
<P>
He said the sanctions are still in place despite Iraq's
fulfillment of all requirements of U.N. Security Council resolution
687, adding that they should accordingly be lifted, starting with
implementation of Paragraph 22 of the resolution 687 as the first
step which provides the lifting of trade embargo.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman thanked, on behalf of Iraqi government, all
those sympathizers, saying that "Iraq would maintain close
contacts with these parties and consult with them to follow
the best ways to achieve the noble goal of removing the
sanctions off Iraq." 
</P>
</TEXT>
