<HEADLINE> Romania: One Million Families in Need of Public Housing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, June 12 (Xinhua) -- Short of public housing, one
million Romanian families are waiting for an apartment from the
government, Nicolae Noica, minister of public works and
territorial planning, said Friday.
</P>
<P>
Over September 1993-May 1998, the government allotted several
hundred million U.S. dollars from the state budget for the
completion of works on 36,147 flats, Noica was quoted as saying by
