<HEADLINE> Chinese Teaching In Tibetan At University </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XINING, June 12 (Xinhua) -- The subjects of algebra, higher
math, mechanics, electromagnetics and atomic physics are now all
available in Tibetan for students at Qinghai Normal University,
something that is regarded as a milestone in Tibetan education.
</P>
<P>
Because of the rapid economic development in recent years,
Tibetans have found themselves in urgent need of Tibetan speakers
in various fields.
</P>
<P>
The Ministry of Education designated Qinghai Normal University
as a place to train bilingual teachers for the Tibet Autonomous
Region and the provinces of Qinghai, Sichuan, Gansu and Yunnan
because it has done a great deal in promoting the use of Tibetan
and in compiling teaching materials in Tibetan.
</P>
<P>
In the past several years, it has compiled and published a
series of teaching materials in more than 500,000 characters.
</P>
<P>
Qinghai Normal has increased the number of majors for Tibetan
students to 14 and bilingual teaching is used in mathematics,
physics, chemistry and Tibetan language.
</P>
<P>
Recent exam results have shown that the Tibetan language method
has greatly stimulated the Tibetan students in their studies and
has improved teaching quality. Tibetans now account for the
largest number of minority students at the university and 26
percent of the total student body.  
</P>
</TEXT>
