<HEADLINE> Shanghai Increasing Consulting Business </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, June 12 (Xinhua) -- The city of Shanghai plans to
expand the scope of its consulting businesses in hopes that they
will contribute 0.45 percent of its GDP with 10 billion yuan in
annual sales, early in the next century.
</P>
<P>
According to local sources, Shanghai had 7,380 companies in the
consulting business, employing 146,000 people, by 1997.
</P>
<P>
The sector generated 3.4 billion yuan in earnings last year, a
rise of 40.6 percent over 1996, making it one of the city's major
service trades, the sources say.
</P>
<P>
The business first got started in 1979, and the city's rapid
economic development has provided a lot of room to develop,
allowing nearly a thousand of the companies to do about two
billion yuan in business annually, accounting for more than half
of the sector's earnings.
</P>
<P>
The city has passed a number of rules and regulations to
standardize the consulting business, and, the end of 1997, had
singled out 125 of the most trustworthy companies and given
licenses to 600 consulting experts.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
