<HEADLINE> Developing Education In Southwestern China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, June 12 (Xinhua) -- A county in southwest China's
Yunnan Province has been working on an educational development
project sponsored by the World Bank.
</P>
<P>
The county has spent 17 million yuan (2 million US dollars) on
the project, 850,000 US dollars of that in a loan from the World
Bank, which began in June 1992.
</P>
<P>
The county has built 45,420 square meters of school buildings,
and bought 9,678 chairs and desks, 450 dorm beds, and 250,000
library books.
</P>
<P>
The county's elementary education system has improved over the
past five years and now provides 99.25 percent of the province's
school-aged children a chance to attend school, a 1.25 percent
increase from 1992.
</P>
<P>
In addition, local educational departments have held a series
of training programs for 1,637 primary and middle school
teachers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
