<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Yunnan, Home to Fir of the Genus Ormosia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, June 12 (Xinhua) -- Chinese foresters have found a
large area of the fir tree of the genus ormosia in a southwestern
province.
</P>
<P>
Specialists say that Yunnan Province has three species of the
tree scattered across 220,000 hectares in northwestern, northern,
northeastern, and southeastern parts of the province.
</P>
<P>
The provincial forestry bureau says that the province has 3.54
million fir trees of this genus, and another 1,204 hectares of the
genus ormosia have been found in Yongsheng County.
</P>
<P>
To protect this rare species, scientists have cultivated more
than 50,000 of them in the Lijiang area, over 2,400 meters above
the sea level.
</P>
<P>
The genus ormosia is a type of ancient tree that is rich in yew
alcohol that has been used to treat certain kinds of cancer like
uterine, lung, and stomach cancer.
</P>
<P>
There are 11 species of this tree in the world, and China has 5
of them. 
</P>
</TEXT>
