<DOCNO> XIE19980612.0213 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Austrian Hero Polster Put it Down to Experience </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
PARIS, June 12 (Xinhua) -- Austrian hero of the match against
Cameroon Toni Polster put the 1-1 draw down to experience.
</P>
<P>
Polster scored a last-minute goal to snatch a 1-1 draw for
Austria. He said on Thursday:"When you've got experience, you know
it's never lost until the final whistle so you keep going."
</P>
<P>
"Overall we played well. We came into the match with great
heart and spirit even if we didn't manage the game very well early
on." said Polster.
</P>
<P>
Polster, a contervisial selection to the Austrian team, said he
didn't have to prove himself any more.
</P>
<P>
Cameroon defender Rigobert Song said:"We were very naive and
maybe that cost us the match. We thought we had the victory in our
pockets and relaxed. We still have a chance especially as everyone
in our group has drawn."
</P>
<P>
Cameroon coach Claude Le Roy was disappointed by the result:'I
think we can be very proud of the team but I'm a little disappointed
that the goal came so soon before the end." 
</P>
</TEXT>
