<HEADLINE> England Coach Rejects Media Criticism </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
PARIS, June 12 (Xinhua) -- England coach Glenn Hoddle has
rejected the media's criticism that he tried to keep his team away
from media exposure.
</P>
<P>
Hoddle was criticised that he was shrouding his squad in a
smokescreen of secrecy after he insisted that the practice match
with French club Caen was played behind closed doors.
</P>
<P>
"There was a misinterpretation of that game. It had nothing at
all to do with keeping the media away." Hoddle argued.
</P>
<P>
"It was just that we wanted to avoid the atmosphere of a 25,000
crowd. It would have inspired the opposition and it would have
affected our players as well." said Hoddle.
</P>
<P>
Hoddle said:"I've been quite amused by the media's reaction to it."
</P>
<P>
But Hoddle refused to reveal who will partner captain Alan
Shearer up front. 
</P>
</TEXT>
