<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Nigeria's World Cup Campaign Upset by Injury, Scuffle </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, June 12 (Xinhua) -- Nigeria's World Cup campaign, which
begins on Saturday with a group game against Spain, has been upset by
the injury of their star striker and internal scuffles.
</P>
<P>
Daniel Amokachi, one of the key Nigerian scorers at the last World
Cup finals four years ago, looks doubtful to spearhead the attack
after injuring his knee in training.
</P>
<P>
The former Everton player in English Premier League is racing
against time to recover in time but his chance to start in the Group C
game would be decided by a fitness test on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Reigning African Footballer of the Viktor Ikpeba, the other top gun
in the team, has stirred controversies by describing the team's
preparations "a shamble".
</P>
<P>
Ikpeba, who helped French club Monaco into semifinals of the
European Cup, was unhappy for being played out of position and
expressed his intention to retire from international football after
the finals.
</P>
<P>
This decision looks ironic since Ikpeba has just forced a place in
the Super Eagles starting line-up in recent matches after years on the
bench.
</P>
<P>
One good news for the Nigerians is that midfielder Nwankwo Kano is
recovering from a stomach upset and should be fit in time for the
game.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile their rival Spain, whose famous national soccer league
makes great contrast to their lacklustre performance in international
competitions, is hoping to erase the tag of underachievers.
</P>
<P>
Spain, quarterfinalist in 1986 and 1994, has never surmount the
barrier beyond last eight.
</P>
<P>
Much will rest on the younger shoulders of 20-year-old Real Madrid
striker Raul Gonzalez, who has won two championship medals.
</P>
<P>
The left-footed forward with great vision and maturity will be
aided in the front by club teammate Fernando Morientes.
</P>
<P>
Morientes made an extraordinary debut against Sweden in March with
two goals in the first five minutes and added two in his second match
against Northern Ireland earlier this month.
</P>
<P>
The man on the goal will probably be 36-year-old Andoni Zubizarreta
who boasts 123 caps and has been the first choice since 1986. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
