<HEADLINE> China's Prices Continue to Drop </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 12 (Xinhua) -- China's price level continued to
edge down in May, according to latest statistics from the
State Development Planning Commission and the State Statistics
Bureau.
</P>
<P>
The retail price index last month decreased by 2.7 percent over
the same month last year and by 1.5 percent over April.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the consumer price index inched down by one percent
on a year-on-year base.
</P>
<P>
During the January-May period, the retail price index and the
consumer price index edged down 1.9 percent and 0.1 percent,
respectively.
</P>
<P>
Only Qinghai Province in northwest China had a slight increase
of 0.2 percent in its retail price index in the first five months
of the year. 
</P>
