<HEADLINE> Electronic Multimedia Advertising System Launched in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, June 12 (Xinhua) -- Malaysia Friday launched a
new medium called the Electronic Multimedia Advertising System
(EMAS), the first system in the region which intersperses
advertisements with real-time news.
</P>
<P>
The new medium is a joint venture project between Interconnect
Communication Private Limited, a local multimedia firm, and
Bernama, the national news agency.
</P>
<P>
The system is fundamentally an electronic advertising network
broadly incorporating IT multimedia and communication technologies
on a Stand-Alone Wide-Area Network (WAN) system to bring
exclusively business advertisers to the public.
</P>
<P>
Its uniqueness is clearly defined by the integrated real-time
on-line news and newsbreaks provided by Bernama as part of the
display.
</P>
<P>
EMAS is aimed at inducing total participation of the Malaysian
business world to advertise electronically at designated high mass
flow congregations such as supermarkets, shopping malls,
hospital/medical centers, banks, transport terminals and
government public service concourses.
</P>
<P>
The system will be installed in six places in the Klang Valley
(Kuala Lumpur and its surrounding areas) before it goes nationwide
next year.
</P>
</TEXT>
