<HEADLINE> Thailand Sets Up Anti-terrorism Center </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, June 12 (Xinhua) -- The Thai government has set up an
anti-terrorism center to ensure that the on-going tourism campaign
"Amazing Thailand 1997-1998" sail through smoothly, a government
news release said Friday.
</P>
<P>
The center, designed to counter international terrorism, has
the status of a task force under the Supreme Command Headquarters
of the Thai Armed Forces.
</P>
<P>
Although it has its line of command, the center will only
start action by the order of the prime minister, said the release,
issued by the government Public Relations Department.
</P>
<P>
Concerned officers from various government agencies have
undergone intensive training courses, with the latest one being
held in Lopburi province, Central Thailand.
</P>
<P>
Supreme Commander General Mongkol Ampornpisit was quoted as
saying that the training course in Lopburi was aimed at ensuring
readiness to take swift action against all kinds of terrorist
activities.
</P>
<P>
He said the center was set up not just to protect the 13th
Asian Games scheduled for later this year but will continue to
exist until the end of next year to cope with possible terrorist
activities.
</P>
<P>
He added that it was not possible to predict an act of
terrorism and that the best thing Thailand could do is to make
good preparations to cope with the situation, should it happens.
</P>
<P>
Thailand launched the "Amazing Thailand" tourism campaign late
last year in the hope of shoring up the economy battered by the
financial crisis. 
</P>
</TEXT>
