<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, June 11 (Xinhua) -- Anson Chan, chief secretary of
China's Hong Kong Special Administrative Region, Thursday urged
the United States to renew the Most Favored Nation (MFN) status
for China to help stabilize the Asian economy.
</P>
<P>
At the Asia Society annual dinner in Washington, Chan also
indicated that Hong Kong's transition had gone "remarkably well"
and its success was due to the commitment of the Chinese central
government in honoring its promise.
</P>
<P>
"Beijing's scrupulous observance of its hand-off policy towards
Hong Kong has been widely recognized both at home and abroad," she
told several hundred guests.
</P>
