removing potential economic instability in Asia by renewing MFN
status for China.
</P>
<P>
U.S. President Bill Clinton had decided early this month that
China be given the MFN status, which is normal trade relationship
between countries. The decision will take effect within 30 days
unless Congress votes against it in the meantime.
</P>
<P>
Some lawmakers, using MFN status for China as a political tool,
oppose Clinton's decision. 
</P>
