solution to the crisis, Yugoslav President Slobodan Milosevic
should continue dialogue with ethnic Albanian leader, Ibrahim
Rugova.
</P>
<P>
Jovanovic also urged Albanian refugees to return home as soon
as possible.
</P>
<P>
Tensions in Kosovo escalated on March 1 when four policemen and
16 Albanians were killed in an armed battle. Since then, more than
250 people have died in clashes between government forces and the
KLA.
</P>
<P>
Ethnic Albanians, who account for 90 percent of the population,
have been seeking independence from Yugoslavia since 1981. 
