<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ukrainian Cabinet Endorses Draft Budget </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KIEV, June 11 (Xinhua) -- The Ukrainian cabinet passed the 1999
draft national budget on Thursday and submitted it to the Supreme
Soviet of Ukraine (parliament) for ratification.
</P>
<P>
The draft budget limits the deficits for the national budget in
1999 to within two percent of the gross domestic product (GDP).
</P>
<P>
The bill stipulates that the budget funds for 1999 will be
primarily spent to further boost domestic production, implement
structural reforms and ensure a rational use of national financial
resources.
</P>
<P>
The bill also highlights legislation on national taxation in a
bid to increase budget revenues. Priority considerations in budget
spending will be given to appropriations for national programs
capable of stimulating economic growth.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, budget spending will also guarantee due payment of
wages to workers in the institutions and businesses covered by the
budget, and social security expenditures on residents.
</P>
<P>
The 1999 budget spending also covers Ukraine's obligation to
repay national debts in a full and due manner.
</P>
<P>
The budget for this year set a deficit of 3.3 percent of the
GDP. The country has been making efforts to reduce the deficit to
2.5 percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
