<HEADLINE> Central America Discusses Expanding Telecom Network </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, June 11 (Xinhua) -- Delegates from Central
American countries met Thursday in Guatemala to discuss expanding
the region's digital telecommunications networks.
</P>
<P>
This meeting, the 89th routine meeting of the board of
directors of the regional Telecommunications Technical Commission
(Comtelca), will define the program to expand the digital network,
said Mario Roberto Paz, Guatemalan telecommunications
superintendent.
</P>
<P>
The project, aiming to improve data transmission in a wider
area, will provide more efficient services to airlines, banks, and
government agencies.
</P>
<P>
The project, financed by the Central American Economic
Integration Bank, will cost 35 million U.S. dollars and be
completed in two years.
</P>
<P>
The ministers of telecommunications of Costa Rica, Guatemala,
El Salvador, Nicaragua, and deputy minister of telecommunications
of Honduras are attending the two-day meeting. 
