<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China to Guarantee Fertilizer Supply </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 12 (Xinhua) -- China is to introduce a new
fertilizer distribution system soon to increase producers' profits
and guarantee supplies for farmers.
</P>
<P>
Under the new system, fertilizer manufacturers will have the
rights to market and sell their products directly to consumers,
rather than acting solely as producers, according to today's China
Daily.
</P>
<P>
Over the last decade, agricultural products companies in charge
of buying fertilizer from producers and selling it to farmers have
played a leading role in fertilizer distribution.
</P>
<P>
More often than not, fertilizer producers have no access to
end-users, resulting in a slow response to the volatile market and
a failure to implement proper pricing strategies.
</P>
<P>
In the first four months of this year, fertilizer production
stood at 8.49 million tons, down 5.9 percent over the same period
last year.
</P>
<P>
The decline in production was primarily caused by sagging
sales, the Beijing-based daily said.
</P>
<P>
High inventory resulting from mounting imports of fertilizer in
the past three consecutive years and a fall in grain prices were
the major culprits behind the production slump.
</P>
<P>
Analysts predict that next year will see a good season for
fertilizer sales.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
