<HEADLINE> China to Readjust Stamp Tax on Securities </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 12 (Xinhua) -- Sources at the State General
Administration of Taxation said that stamp tax on securities will
be readjusted beginning today.
</P>
<P>
All parties involved in the transaction, inheritance and
presentation of securities should turn in 0.4 percent stamp tax
instead of 0.5 percent, respectively, according to the sum
calculated according to the transaction prices of the day when the
related documents are drawn up.
</P>
<P>
Following the readjustment, central finance will obtain 88
percent of the tax and local finance, 12 percent, the same as
before, the sources said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
