<BODY>
<HEADLINE> World Bank Backs Ghana's Economic Reform Support </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, June 11 (Xinhua) -- The World Bank approved here
Thursday a 50 million U.S. dollars interest-free credit for the
economic reform support operation project in Ghana.
</P>
<P>
This project will support the reforms in the public sector,
public expenditure management, privatization, and the energy and
cocoa sectors.
</P>
<P>
Completion of the project will enable the government of Ghana
to substantially improve fiscal performance and thus help maintain
a stable macroeconomic framework necessary to achieve sustained
broad-based, private sector-led growth and reduce poverty.
</P>
<P>
The credit will be channeled through the International
Development Association (IDA), the World Bank's concessional
lending arm for developing countries.  
</P>
</TEXT>
