<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Eastern Chinese Province Producing Biodegradable Plastic </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HEFEI, June 12 (Xinhua) -- East China's Anhui Province has
begun to produce a type of biodegradable plastic sheet that can
help solve the "white pollution" problem and better protect the
environment.
</P>
<P>
The plastic sheet, developed by Professor Qian Jun of Hefei
United University after ten years of research, doesn't harm the
environment and it can be used to protect crops from viruses.
</P>
<P>
China has long had a problem with "white pollution", the
wide-spread use of styrofoam containers, because they don't
decompose in the environment easily.
</P>
<P>
The Anhui provincial government announced that the first-phase
of a project to produce 30,000 tons of this decomposable plastic
material was completed in the city of Huaibei recently.
</P>
<P>
The environment-friendly plastic has extensive applications to
agriculture, industry, and daily-use items. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
