<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> First Brazil Match Does Not Satisfy Pele </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO, June 11 (Xinhua) -- Pele, considered the best
soccer football player of the century, said that the first match
of the Brazilian team against Scotland did not satisfy him and
said that the selection was not at its best.
</P>
<P>
Brazil defeated Scotland 2-1 in the inaugural game of the
France 98 Soccer World Cup.
</P>
<P>
Pele commented that the selection of his country did not play
well, despite an improvement in the second half of the match, with
the change of Leonardo instead of Giovani, middlefielder.
</P>
<P>
However, he said that the victory is good and that it is
necessary for the Brazilian selection to correct its mistakes for
the next match with the Morocco selection next June 16.
</P>
<P>
Edson Arantes DO Nascimento "Pele" said that it was a mistake
of trainer Zagallo not to consider forward Edmundo for the
inaugural game. According to Pele, Edmundo would have been a good
choice to defeat the Scotish persecution.
</P>
<P>
Pele is a commentarist with the Brazilian TV network Globo
during the France 98 World Cup. 
</P>
</TEXT>
