<HEADLINE> Britain to Showcase Its Millennium Building </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, June 11 (Xinhua) -- The British government Thursday
launched a touring exhibition of twelve millennium building to
show the rest of the world how the UK is preparing for the new
century.
</P>
<P>
The "12 for 2000 - Building for the Millennium" exhibition,
which will be taken around the world before the year 2000, "is a
reflection of the UK on the verge of the 21st century", said Chris
Smith, Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport.
</P>
<P>
Under the headline themes of regeneration, environment and
people, the exhibition includes computer animation, video,
photography, CD-ROM, plans and drawings.
</P>
<P>
Chris Smith, also the chairman of the UK Millennium Commission,
which was set up to assist the communities in celebrating the
start of the new millennium, added that the twelve building are
only a sample of the hundreds of projects being developed across
the UK.
</P>
<P>
No other country in the world is investing as much as the UK to
mark the new millennium. The Millennium Commission is planning to
make 2 billion pounds (3.2 billion U.S. dollars) available to
support projects in Scotland, Wales, England and Northern Ireland,
according to Chris Smith.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
