<HEADLINE> Greek Teachers Clash With Riot Police </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, June 11 (Xinhua) -- Greek teachers Thursday clashed
with riot police when they tried to occupy the examination centers
around the country in a bid to stop their colleagues from taking
part in the test for new appointments to state schools.
</P>
<P>
Despite police being stationed at all the 32 centers,
protesting teachers have managed to take over the centers in
Athens, Thessaloniki, Pyrgos, Agrinio, Kozani and Rhodes.
</P>
<P>
In the Athens suburb of Pefki, one policeman was slightly
injured and two teachers were arrested when about 70 teachers
tried to break through a police guard.
</P>
<P>
In Patissia, four teachers were arrested and some vehicles
parked in the area were damaged when teachers used sticks and
stones to break through another school acting as examination
center. Riot police dispersed them by firing tear gas.
</P>
<P>
Greek teachers began Thursday a two-day nationwide strike to
protest the government's new hiring examination system.  
</P>
</TEXT>
