<DOCNO> XIE19980612.0342 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> UNDP Assists Mongolia in Market Economy Transition </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, June 11 (Xinhua) -- The United Nations
Development Programme (UNDP) and the Government of Mongolia have
signed a 2.6 million U.S. dollars project agreement, a release
from UNDP said on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The project agreement is aimed to help smooth the country's
transition to a market system economy and create a more dynamic
private sector.
</P>
<P>
Market reform policies and privatization programs have recently
been introduced in Mongolia to improve the economy. Many private
enterprises have suffered because of their inexperience with the
market system.
</P>
<P>
UNDP assistance will focus on the needs of 10 newly privatized
companies for modern management techniques and staff training. 
</P>
</TEXT>
